{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:17:28.105Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Conditional Independence Assumption"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the core \"naive\" part of Naive Bayes classifiers — it assumes that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all features are independent of each other given the class label"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", meaning that knowing one feature provides no additional information about another feature once you already know the class."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Conditional Independence Assumption — concept overview"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Definition of conditional independence:\nGiven three random variables X, Y, and Z:\n- X and Y are conditionally independent given Z if:\n$$P(X, Y | Z) = P(X | Z) \\times P(Y | Z)$$"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In plain terms"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- X and Y being independent given Z means that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "knowledge of Z does not influence the relationship between X and Y"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Once you know the class (Z), features (X and Y) don't depend on each other"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Naive Bayes Assumption"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a Naive Bayes classifier with features "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X_1, X_2,..., X_d"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and class "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Y"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Assumption"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$P(X_1, X_2,..., X_d | Y) = \\prod"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^{d} P(X_i | Y)$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Translated"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Features "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X_j"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "conditionally independent given Y"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", for all "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "i \\neq j"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- The probability of all features given the class equals the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "product of individual feature probabilities"}, {"type": "text", "text": " given the class"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why it's called \"naive\""}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- It's a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "strong assumption"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that may not hold in reality\n- True dependencies between features may deviate from this assumption\n- Despite being \"naive,\" it still performs well on many datasets"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Simplifies the Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Without conditional independence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- You'd need to estimate the joint probability "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "P(X_1, X_2,..., X_d | Y)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- This requires estimating "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "exponentially many parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (one for every combination of feature values)\n- For d binary features: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "2^{d}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " parameters per class"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "With conditional independence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- You only need to estimate individual probabilities: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "P(X_i | Y)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for each feature\n- Requires only "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "d parameters per class"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (linear complexity)\n- Much simpler and computationally feasible"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example: Email Spam Classification"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scenario"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Classify email as Spam (Y=1) or Not Spam (Y=0)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Features"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X_1"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Contains word \"free\"\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X_2"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Contains word \"money\"\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X_3"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Contains word \"urgent\""}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Naive Bayes assumption"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Given that the email is spam, the presence of \"free\" is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "independent"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of the presence of \"money\"\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "P(X_1, X_2, X_3 | Y=\\text{spam}) = P(X_1|\\text{spam}) \\times P(X_2|\\text{spam}) \\times P(X_3|\\text{spam})"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In reality"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- This assumption is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "hardly ever true"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for terms in documents\n- Words like \"free\" and \"money\" are often correlated (both appear in spam)\n- Knowledge of \"free\" being present "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "does"}, {"type": "text", "text": " give information about \"money\" being present"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Despite this"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Naive Bayes still performs well on many datasets\n- The simplification makes it practical and fast"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Advantages of the Assumption"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Advantage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simpl"}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "2^{d}"}}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "implement"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Easy to calculate probabilities"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fast computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only need individual feature probabilities"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Few parameters"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linear complexity (d parameters vs. $2^d$)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Works with small data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Doesn't require massive datasets to estimate joint probabilities"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Effective"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Still performs well despite being \"naive\""}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitations of the Assumption"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rarely true in reality"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Features are often correlated (e.g., words in documents)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ignores feature dependencies"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Misses relationships between features"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "May reduce accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When correlations are strong, model may be less accurate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overestimates probabilities"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Product of probabilities can overestimate joint probability"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When It Works Well"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The assumption works surprisingly well when:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Features are mostly independent"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., different sensor readings)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Correlations are weak"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (mild correlations don't hurt much)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large number of features"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (individual probabilities dominate)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classification task"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is not extremely sensitive to exact probabilities"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Conditional Independence Assumption"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": All features are independent given the class label"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "P(X_1,..., X_d | Y) = \\prod P(X_i | Y)"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Once you know the c"}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "2^{d}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " features don't depend on each other"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why \"naive\""}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Strong assumption that rarely holds true in reality"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simplification"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Reduces exponential parameters to linear (d vs. $2^d$)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefit"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Simple, fast, works with small data despite being \"wrong\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ignores feature correlations (e.g., \"free\" and \"money\" in spam)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reality"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Features are often correlated, but Naive Bayes still performs well"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Conditional Independence Assumption is the \"simplifying cheat\" that makes Naive Bayes work — by assuming all features are independent once you know the class, it reduces the impossible task of estimating joint probabilities for all feature combinations to the simple task of estimating individual feature probabilities, making the model fast, simple, and practical despite being technically \"wrong\" because features are often correlated in real data."}]}]}}